memory.limit(size = 16000)  
## [1] Inf
corpus <- Corpus(VectorSource(bbc$text))

corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transformer(tolower))
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removePunctuation)
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeNumbers)
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeWords, stopwords("english"))
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, stemDocument)
dtm <- DocumentTermMatrix(corpus)
dtm_matrix <- as.matrix(dtm)

word_frequencies <- colSums(dtm_matrix)
sorted_words <- sort(word_frequencies, decreasing = TRUE)

threshold <- quantile(sorted_words, 0.15)
dtm_reduced <- dtm_matrix[, word_frequencies > threshold]
feature_vector_2205 <- dtm_reduced[2205, ]
feature_vector_2205 <- feature_vector_2205[feature_vector_2205 >= 4]
print(feature_vector_2205)

#Question 2:

freq <- colSums(dtm_matrix)
terms <- names(sort(freq, decreasing = TRUE)[1:3000])
dtm_reduced <- dtm_matrix[, terms]
print(paste("Number of features after frequency  is: ", ncol(dtm_reduced)))
## [1] "Number of features after frequency  is:  3000"
correlation_matrix <- cor(dtm_reduced)
high_correlation <- caret::findCorrelation(correlation_matrix, cutoff = 0.9)
dtm_final <- dtm_reduced[,-high_correlation]
print(paste("Final number of features:", ncol(dtm_final)))
## [1] "Final number of features: 2979"
print(paste("Features removed by correlation analysis are :", length(high_correlation)))
## [1] "Features removed by correlation analysis are : 21"
y <- factor(bbc$category)

set.seed(42)
train_index <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
X_train <- dtm_final[train_index, ]
X_test <- dtm_final[-train_index, ]
y_train <- y[train_index]
y_test <- y[-train_index]

#Logistic Regression :

train_df <- as.data.frame(X_train)
test_df <- as.data.frame(X_test)
train_df$category <- y_train

mlr_model <- multinom(category~., data = train_df,
                      MaxNWts = 50000,maxit = 1000,
                      trace = FALSE,decay = 0.1)

mlr_pred <- predict(mlr_model, newdata = test_df)

mlr_confusionmatrix <- confusionMatrix(factor(mlr_pred), y_test)
print("\nMultinomial Logistic Regression Results:")

plot_confusion_matrix <- function(cm, title) {
cm_df <- as.data.frame(as.table(cm$table))
names(cm_df) <- c("True", "Predicted", "Freq")
ggplot(cm_df, aes(x = Predicted, y = True, fill = Freq)) +
geom_tile() +
geom_text(aes(label = Freq)) +
scale_fill_gradient(low = "yellow", high = "orange") +
theme_minimal() +
labs(title = title,
x = "Predicted Category",
y = "True Category") +
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
}
print(plot_confusion_matrix(nb_confusionmatrix, "Naive Bayes Confusion Matrix"))

print(plot_confusion_matrix(mlr_confusionmatrix, "Logistic Regression Confusion Matrix"))

metrics_comparison <- rbind(
transform(nb_metrics, Model = "Naive Bayes"),
transform(mlr_metrics, Model = "Logistic Regression")
)

ggplot(metrics_comparison, aes(x = Category, y = Precision, fill = Model)) +
geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
theme_minimal() +
labs(title = "Precision Comparison by Category") +
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

ggplot(metrics_comparison, aes(x = Category, y = Recall, fill = Model)) +
geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
theme_minimal() +
labs(title = "Recall Comparison by Category") +
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
